In an Active/Standby configuration, one instance is active while the other remains idle until a failure occurs.

The standby instance takes over when the active one fails.

For example, a primary server handles traffic while a backup server waits for failover.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is disaster recovery systems.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is database replication setups.

This model ensures reliability but may underutilize resources.
